{"lemma":"سَجِين","slug":"سَجِين","root":"س.ج.ن","root_slug":"س-ج-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ج-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَجِين","root":"سجن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19005","n19007"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prisoner, inmate"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"imprisoned"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"The meaning of this term is uncertain. Possibilities include","examples":[{"text":"كَلَّا إِنَّ كِتَابَ الْفُجَّارِ لَفِي سِجِّينٍ / وَمَا أَدْرَاكَ مَا سِجِّينٌ / كِتَابٌ مَّرْقُومٌ","english":"No! Indeed, the record of the wicked is in sijjeen. And what can make you know what is sijjeen? It is [their destination recorded in] a register inscribed."}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"The meaning of this term is uncertain. Possibilities include:; the Underworld, a bottomless pit, an infernal prison, Hades, Sheol, the abyss, often depicted under the seven Earths."},{"pos":"name","gloss":"The meaning of this term is uncertain. Possibilities include:; Hell"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"The meaning of this term is uncertain. Possibilities include:; Hell; The lowest hellhole in the Hell"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"The meaning of this term is uncertain. Possibilities include:; the seventh Earth"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"The meaning of this term is uncertain. Possibilities include:; the record of the wicked"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"The meaning of this term is uncertain. Possibilities include:; an intensive/diminutive form of سِجْن (sijn, “prison”)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Unknown, possible an invented word on the basis of سِجْن (sijn) and analogical to عِلِّيِّين (ʕilliyyīn), compare also سَجَنْجَل (sajanjal); the definition given by the Qurʔān itself as كِتَابٌ مَرْقُومٌ (kitābun marqūmun) may even be due to glossema."},"ipa":["/sa.d͡ʒiːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19005","headword_ar":"سَجِينٌ","root":"sjn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masojuwnN","text_ar":"مَسْجُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Imprisoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujanaA='u","text_ar":"سُجَنَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajonaY","text_ar":"سَجْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": and is applied to a female likewise, as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajiynapN","text_ar":"سَجِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajonaY","text_ar":"سَجْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajaAy^inu","text_ar":"سَجَايِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19007","headword_ar":"سِجِّينٌ","root":"sjn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sijonN","text_ar":"سِجْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [In the Kur lxxxiii. 7,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain place in which is the record"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the deeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the wicked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;) or, as I 'Ab says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which are their registers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AO says, it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiE~iylN","text_ar":"فِعِّيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ijonu","text_ar":"السِّجْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfis~iyqu","text_ar":"الفِسِّيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfisoqu","text_ar":"الفِسْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain valley in Hell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain stone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seventh earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) [these explanations are given by those who hold that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA sij~iynN","text_ar":"مَا سِجِّينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the next verse is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kitaAbu","text_ar":"مَا كِتَابُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sij~iynK","text_ar":"سِجِّينٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or it there means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a register comprising the deeds of the wicked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii, and of mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the devils and the unbelievers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA sj~yn","text_ar":"ما سجّين"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the next verse is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA ktAb sj~yn","text_ar":"ما كتاب سجّين"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the meaning is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is beneath the seventh earth, the abode of Iblees and his forces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) IAth says, it occurs in a trad. with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and without that article it is a proper name for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Hell"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and hence the mention of it in the Kur lxxxiii. 7. (L.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sij~iylN","text_ar":"سِجِّيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  Also Anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard, vehement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;) applied to a beating. (S, L.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Continuing, lasting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"everlasting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^imN","text_ar":"دَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sij~iylN","text_ar":"سِجِّيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so accord. to El-Muärrij. (L. [See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sij~iylN","text_ar":"سِجِّيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAniyap","text_ar":"عَلَانِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, K:) so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamila *`lika sij~iynFA","text_ar":"عَمِلَ ذٰلِكَ سِجِّينًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did that openly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"publicly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.)       -A4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Palm-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxol","text_ar":"نَخْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silotiyn","text_ar":"سِلْتِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, L, K) in the dial. of the people of El-Bahreyn; (As, L;) [app. meaning that the latter word is of that dial.; for it is said that] the Arabs [app. the Arabs in general] say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sij~iyn","text_ar":"سِجِّين"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silotiyn","text_ar":"سِلْتِين"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is not Arabic: (L:) the palm-trees thus termed are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as have trenches dug at their feet to conduct the water to them when it has not reached  to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sltn","text_ar":"سلتن"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","Bd","Jel","As"]}]}}